"title": "7145: remnant",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7145",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A small group of people who remain faithful to God, despite widespread unbelief or faithlessness around them. God preserves a remnant in order to ensure a renewed and restored people in the future.</p>\n<h2>God preserves a remnant of his people</h2>\n<h3>Noah and his family</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen7:23\">GEN 7:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen6:7-Gen6:8\">GEN 6:7–6:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen6:18\">GEN 6:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen7:1\">GEN 7:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen7:7\">GEN 7:7</a></p>\n<h3>Joseph and the sons of Israel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen45:7\">GEN 45:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen50:20\">GEN 50:20</a></p>\n<h3>Seven thousand faithful in Israel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs19:18\">1KI 19:18</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Survivors of Assyria's invasion of Judah</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs19:4\">2KI 19:4</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa37:4\">ISA 37:4</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs18:13\">2KI 18:13</a></p>\n<h3>Survivors of the destruction of Israel</h3>\n<p>People from the northern kingdom of Israel who had moved to Judah and so escaped its destruction by Assyria:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr11:14\">2CH 11:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr15:9\">2CH 15:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr31:6\">2CH 31:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr34:9\">2CH 34:9</a></p>\n<h3>Judah as the remnant of God's people</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs17:18\">2KI 17:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs21:14\">2KI 21:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr34:21\">2CH 34:21</a></p>\n<h3>Survivors of the fall of Jerusalem</h3>\n<p>Those taken as exiles into Babylon:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs25:11\">2KI 25:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr36:20\">2CH 36:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs25:12\">2KI 25:12</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer39:10\">JER 39:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs25:22-2Kgs25:23\">2KI 25:22–25:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer40:11-Jer40:12\">JER 40:11–40:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer40:15\">JER 40:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer42:2\">JER 42:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer43:5\">JER 43:5</a></p>\n<h3>Those who returned after the exile</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra9:8\">EZR 9:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra2:1-Ezra2:2\">EZR 2:1–2:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra9:13\">EZR 9:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh1:2\">NEH 1:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hag1:12-Hag1:14\">HAG 1:12–1:14</a></p>\n<h3>Those waiting for Jesus Christ's coming</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:25\">LUK 2:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:38\">LUK 2:38</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:12\">JHN 1:12</a></p>\n<h2>The remnant as the few who escape judgment</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut4:27\">DEU 4:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa10:22\">ISA 10:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom9:27\">ROM 9:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer6:9\">JER 6:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer44:14\">JER 44:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer44:28\">JER 44:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek5:12\">EZK 5:12</a>EZK <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek9:8\">9:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek11:13\">EZK 11:13</a>\n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek17:21\">EZK 17:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos3:12\">AMO 3:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos5:3\">AMO 5:3</a></p>\n<h2>God's promise of hope and restoration</h2>\n<h3>Hope for a remnant seen in the coming of the Messiah</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa11:1\">ISA 11:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa6:13\">ISA 6:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer23:5\">JER 23:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech3:8\">ZEC 3:8</a></p>\n<h3>God's promise that survivors will remain</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa4:2-Isa4:3\">ISA 4:2–4:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:9\">ISA 1:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom9:29\">ROM 9:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa17:6\">ISA 17:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa37:31-Isa37:32\">ISA 37:31–37:32</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs19:30-2Kgs19:31\">2KI 19:30–19:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek14:22\">EZK 14:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:32\">JOL 2:32</a></p>\n<h2>Themes associated with the remnant</h2>\n<h3>The land restored to the remnant of God's people</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa27:12-Isa27:13\">ISA 27:12–27:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph2:7-Zeph2:10\">ZEP 2:7–2:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech8:6-Zech8:12\">ZEC 8:6–8:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech10:9\">ZEC 10:9</a></p>\n<h3>A second exodus</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa4:5-Isa4:6\">ISA 4:5–4:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa10:26\">ISA 10:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa11:11\">ISA 11:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa11:15-Isa11:16\">ISA 11:15–11:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa31:5\">ISA 31:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer16:14-Jer16:15\">JER 16:14–16:15</a></p>\n<h3>Restoration of the people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa10:20-Isa10:21\">ISA 10:20–10:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa11:12\">ISA 11:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa28:5\">ISA 28:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa35:8-Isa35:10\">ISA 35:8–35:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa46:3-Isa46:4\">ISA 46:3–46:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:7\">JER 31:7</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer23:3\">JER 23:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic2:12\">MIC 2:12</a></p>\n<h2>Further promises associated with the remnant</h2>\n<h3>The promise of future hope</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa60:21-Isa60:22\">ISA 60:21–60:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa61:4-Isa61:6\">ISA 61:4–61:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel3:1\">JOL 3:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic4:6-Mic4:7\">MIC 4:6–4:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic5:7-Mic5:9\">MIC 5:7–5:9</a></p>\n<h3>God's promise of forgiveness to the remnant</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer50:20\">JER 50:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa33:24\">ISA 33:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:34\">JER 31:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer33:7-Jer33:8\">JER 33:7–33:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic7:18\">MIC 7:18</a></p>\n<h3>A renewed relationship with God</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer24:5-Jer24:7\">JER 24:5–24:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer32:37-Jer32:40\">JER 32:37–32:40</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph3:12-Zeph3:17\">ZEP 3:12–3:17</a></p>\n<h3>The need for faithful obedience</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:19\">ISA 1:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer42:6-Jer42:10\">JER 42:6–42:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer44:7-Jer44:8\">JER 44:7–44:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra9:14\">EZR 9:14</a></p>\n<h2>The remnant as heirs of God's new covenant</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:2\">JER 31:2</a> <em>The promise of the new covenant is made to the surviving remnant of Israel</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:31-Jer31:33\">JER 31:31–31:33</a></p>\n<h3>A faithful remnant among the Jews</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom11:5\">ROM 11:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:16\">LUK 1:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:32\">LUK 12:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom11:7\">ROM 11:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom11:15\">ROM 11:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom11:23\">ROM 11:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom11:25-Rom11:26\">ROM 11:25–11:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas1:1\">JAS 1:1</a></p>\n<h3>A faithful remnant from among the Gentiles</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa56:6-Isa56:8\">ISA 56:6–56:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech14:16\">ZEC 14:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:16\">JHN 10:16</a> <em>Jesus Christ's other sheep are believing Gentiles who will be gathered with the believers of Israel</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:17\">ACT 15:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos9:12\">AMO 9:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom11:17\">ROM 11:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph3:6\">EPH 3:6</a></p>\n<h3>God's new Israel includes all believers</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:28\">MAT 19:28</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:30\">LUK 22:30</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:16\">GAL 6:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:1\">1PE 1:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:9\">1PE 2:9</a></p>\n<h2>Other references to a surviving remnant</h2>\n<p>Og, king of Bashan, only survivor of the Rephaites:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut3:11\">DEU 3:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh13:12\">JOS 13:12</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg20:46-Judg20:47\">JDG 20:46–20:47</a> <em>survivors from the tribe of Benjamin</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr18:16\">2CH 18:16</a> <em>the scattered remains of Israel's army under Ahab</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa16:4\">ISA 16:4</a> <em>fugitives from Moab</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa21:16-Isa21:17\">ISA 21:16–21:17</a> <em>few survivors from Kedar</em></p>",
